# Authorization Patterns

## Overview

Our authorization system implements role-based access control (RBAC) with fine-grained permissions:

- Role-based access control
- Permission management
- Resource-level access
- Policy enforcement
- Audit logging

## Core Technologies

- Custom RBAC system
- Policy-based access control
- Resource ownership
- Permission inheritance
- Audit trails

## Implementation

### 1. Role Management

```typescript
// auth/roles.ts
export const Roles = {
  ADMIN: 'admin',
  USER: 'user',
  GUEST: 'guest',
} as const;

export type Role = keyof typeof Roles;

export const RolePermissions: Record<Role, string[]> = {
  admin: ['*'],
  user: ['read:own', 'write:own', 'delete:own'],
  guest: ['read:public'],
};
```

### 2. Permission Checking

```typescript
// auth/permissions.ts
export function checkPermission(
  user: User,
  resource: Resource,
  action: string,
): boolean {
  // Check role-based permissions
  const permissions = RolePermissions[user.role];
  if (permissions.includes('*')) {
    return true;
  }

  // Check resource ownership
  if (resource.ownerId === user.id && permissions.includes(`${action}:own`)) {
    return true;
  }

  // Check public access
  if (resource.isPublic && permissions.includes(`${action}:public`)) {
    return true;
  }

  return false;
}
```

### 3. Authorization Middleware

```typescript
// auth/middleware.ts
export function requirePermission(action: string) {
  return async (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
    try {
      const resource = await getResource(req.params.id);
      if (!checkPermission(req.user, resource, action)) {
        throw new AuthorizationError('Insufficient permissions');
      }
      next();
    } catch (error) {
      next(error);
    }
  };
}
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Role Management

- Define clear role hierarchy
- Implement role inheritance
- Document permissions
- Regular role review
- Principle of least privilege

### 2. Access Control

- Resource-level permissions
- Ownership validation
- Public/private resources
- Permission inheritance
- Access auditing

### 3. Security

- Validate all access
- Log authorization attempts
- Monitor suspicious activity
- Regular permission review
- Security testing

### 4. Implementation

- Clear error messages
- Proper logging
- Performance optimization
- Caching strategies
- Scalable design

